%N A395954 Decimal expansion of the median distance from the center of a unit disk to a line that passes through two points independently and uniformly selected at random in the disk.
%C A395954 The median of the probability distributed function f(x) = (16/(3*Pi))*(1-x^2)^(3/2) for 0 <= x <= 1, and 0 otherwise.
%C A395954 The real root of the equation x*(5-2*x^2)*sqrt(1-x^2) + 3*arcsin(x) = 3*Pi/4.
%D A395954 A. M. Mathai, An Introduction to Geometrical Probability: Distributional Aspects with Applications, Amsterdam: Gordon and Breach, 1999, p. 205.
%e A395954 0.309072512588585114915620861503569959238319778268016...
%t A395954 RealDigits[x /. FindRoot[x*(5-2*x^2)*Sqrt[1-x^2] + 3*ArcSin[x] == 3*Pi/4, {x, 1/2}, WorkingPrecision -> 120]][[1]]
%o A395954 (PARI) solve(x = 0, 1, x*(5-2*x^2)*sqrt(1-x^2) + 3*asin(x) - 3*Pi/4)
%Y A395954 Cf. A395953 (mean), A395955, A395956.
